{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871486750,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3067be001iX0zUYMaXsNTiX","messageID":"msg_d7a305452001vOCdpEE47yh6Jm","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_00e04b33a13f49d1bb7fe0db","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775871486734,"end":1775871486748}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871486763,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3063fd001bSXjPba236St7Q","messageID":"msg_d7a305452001vOCdpEE47yh6Jm","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d1c1abd4833544b4a879ef1b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-030\n10: - **Module**: `manifests`\n11: - **Language**: YAML\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: - **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: AgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Requirements\n24: \n25: ### AR-030-001: Chart 结构与元数据\n26: \n27: The Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-A — Chart.yaml 包含正确的元数据\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\n32: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL pass without errors\n34: - **AND** the chart SHALL have `name: agentcube` and `version: 0.1.0` in Chart.yaml\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-B — values.yaml 包含所有必需配置项\n37: \n38: - **GIVEN** the `values.yaml` file exists in the chart\n39: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL contain keys for `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `workloadmanager.*`, `router.*`, and `volcano.scheduler.*`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-C — 目录结构完整\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the chart directory structure exists\n45: - **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL contain: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/`, and `crds/`\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### AR-030-002: Helm 安装与 Namespace 管理\n51: \n52: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation.\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-A — Helm install 创建 namespace\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n57: - **AND** `redis.addr` is set to a valid Redis address in values\n58: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace` is executed\n59: - **THEN** the namespace `agentcube` SHALL be created\n60: - **AND** all resources SHALL be deployed to that namespace\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-B — Helm upgrade 成功渲染模板\n63: \n64: - **GIVEN** the chart is already installed\n65: - **AND** values are provided with required `redis.addr`\n66: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube` runs\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL succeed without manual editing of rendered YAML\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### AR-030-003: Redis 环境变量注入\n72: \n73: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-A — Workload Manager 接收 Redis 配置\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` and `redis.password: secret123` are set in values\n78: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod starts\n79: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n80: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD=secret123` environment variable\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-B — Router 接收 Redis 配置\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` is set in values\n85: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n86: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n87: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values (empty string if not set)\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-C — Redis 密码可为空\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is set and `redis.password` is omitted or empty\n92: - **WHEN** pods start\n93: - **THEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` SHALL be set to empty string `\"\"`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ### AR-030-004: Workload Manager Deployment 配置\n98: \n99: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with configurable replica count, image, service type, resources, health probes, and environment variables.\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-A — 默认副本数\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n104: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n105: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-B — 自定义副本数\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.replicas: 3` in values\n110: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n111: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-C — 容器镜像可配置\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.image.repository: my-registry/workloadmanager` and `image.tag: v1.0.0` in values\n116: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n117: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/workloadmanager:v1.0.0`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-D — Service 端口配置\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.service.port: 9090` in values\n122: - **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port `9090`\n124: - **AND** targetPort SHALL match the container port\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-E — 健康检查探针\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n129: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod is created\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL have a livenessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n131: - **AND** a readinessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-F — 资源限制可配置\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: \"2\"` and `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: \"2Gi\"` in values\n136: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n137: - **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-G — 额外环境变量\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.extraEnv: [{\"name\": \"CUSTOM_VAR\", \"value\": \"custom-value\"}]` in values\n142: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n143: - **THEN** the container SHALL include `CUSTOM_VAR` environment variable\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### AR-030-005: Router Deployment 配置\n148: \n149: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, ClusterIP service, resources, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing to the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-A — Router 默认副本数\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n154: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n155: - **THEN** the Router `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-B — Router 连接到 Workload Manager\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube` and Workload Manager service port `8080`\n160: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-C — Router 镜像可配置\n164: \n165: - **GIVEN** `router.image.repository: my-registry/agentcube-router` and `image.tag: latest` in values\n166: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n167: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/agentcube-router:latest`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-D — Router Service 类型可配置\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** `router.service.type: LoadBalancer` in values\n172: - **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL have `type: LoadBalancer`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-E — Router 健康检查\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n178: - **WHEN** the Router pod is created\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL have livenessProbe on `/health/live`\n180: - **AND** readinessProbe on `/health/ready`\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-F — Router 资源限制\n183: \n184: - **GIVEN** `router.resources.limits.cpu: \"1\"` and `router.resources.limits.memory: \"1Gi\"` in values\n185: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n186: - **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-G — Router 调试模式\n189: \n190: - **GIVEN** `router.debug: true` in values\n191: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n192: - **THEN** the container args SHALL include `--debug`\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### AR-030-006: Workload Manager RBAC\n197: \n198: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the required permissions for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-A — ServiceAccount 创建\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** chart installation\n203: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n204: - **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the release namespace\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-B — ClusterRole 权限\n207: \n208: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n209: - **WHEN** the ClusterRole is created\n210: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n211:   - `sandboxes` (CRD) - all verbs\n212:   - `sandboxclaims` (CRD) - all verbs\n213:   - `codeinterpreters` (CRD) - all verbs\n214:   - `agentruntimes` (CRD) - all verbs\n215:   - `pods` (core) - list, watch, delete\n216:   - `secrets` (core) - get, list, watch, create, update, delete\n217:   - `tokenreviews` (authentication.k8s.io) - create\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-C — ClusterRoleBinding 绑定\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `agentcube`\n222: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n223: - **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager` SHALL bind `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `agentcube` to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### AR-030-007: Router 命名空间 RBAC (可选)\n228: \n229: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-A — RBAC 默认禁用\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false` (default)\n234: - **WHEN** templates render\n235: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-B — RBAC 启用时创建\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` in values\n240: - **AND** `router.serviceAccountName: agentcube-router` (or defaulted)\n241: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n242: - **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created\n243: - **AND** a `Role` granting secrets verbs SHALL be created in the release namespace\n244: - **AND** a `RoleBinding` SHALL bind the ServiceAccount to the Role\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-C — Router 使用专用 ServiceAccount\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa` in values\n249: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n250: - **THEN** the Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa`\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### AR-030-008: Volcano Agent Scheduler (可选)\n255: \n256: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-A — 默认不启用\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n261: - **WHEN** templates render\n262: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-B — 启用时创建资源\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true` in values\n267: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n268: - **THEN** it SHALL create:\n269:   - `ServiceAccount` for the scheduler\n270:   - `ConfigMap` with agent-scheduler configuration\n271:   - `ClusterRole` with Volcano scheduling permissions\n272:   - `ClusterRoleBinding` for the scheduler\n273:   - `Service` for the scheduler\n274:   - `Deployment` for the scheduler\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-C — Volcano 镜像可配置\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: custom-volcano/agent-scheduler` in values\n279: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n280: - **THEN** the container image SHALL use that repository\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### AR-030-009: CRD 清单\n285: \n286: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` in the chart's `crds/` directory.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-A — CRD 目录存在\n289: \n290: - **GIVEN** the chart exists\n291: - **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n292: - **THEN** a `crds/` directory SHALL exist with CRD YAML files\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-B — AgentRuntime CRD\n295: \n296: - **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n297: - **WHEN** the `agentruntimes` CRD is applied\n298: - **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n299: - **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n300: - **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-C — CodeInterpreter CRD\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n305: - **WHEN** the `codeinterpreters` CRD is applied\n306: - **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n307: - **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n308: - **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ### AR-030-010: Helm 模板验证\n313: \n314: The chart SHALL pass Helm validation and render correctly.\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-A — Helm lint 通过\n317: \n318: - **GIVEN** the chart at `manifests/charts/base/`\n319: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n320: - **THEN** it SHALL exit with code 0 (success)\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-B — 模板渲染无错误\n323: \n324: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is provided\n325: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` runs\n326: - **THEN** it SHALL render without errors\n327: - **AND** produce valid Kubernetes YAML\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-C — 完整渲染包含所有资源\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** all required values are provided\n332: - **AND** `router.rbac.create: true` and `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n333: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n334: - **THEN** output SHALL include:\n335:   - WorkloadManager Deployment and Service\n336:   - Router Deployment and Service\n337:   - WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n338:   - Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n339:   - Volcano scheduler resources\n340:   - CRDs installed via `crds/` directory\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Non-Requirements\n345: \n346: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n347: \n348: - Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n349: - Ingress configuration\n350: - Prometheus/Grafana monitoring stack\n351: - Redis deployment (external dependency)\n352: - Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n353: - Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n354: - Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n355: - Custom Ingress or NetworkPolicy configurations\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Dependencies\n360: \n361: | Dependency | Description |\n362: |------------|-------------|\n363: | deployment/spec.md | Base deployment requirements |\n364: | deployment/design.md | Helm chart specification |\n365: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ | CRD type definitions (source for generated CRDs) |\n366: | Helm 3 | Chart rendering and installation |\n367: | Kubernetes 1.19+ | API versions used |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Acceptance Criteria\n372: \n373: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n374: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n375: | AC030-001 | Chart.yaml renders with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 | `helm lint` |\n376: | AC030-002 | values.yaml contains all documented keys with correct defaults | YAML parsing |\n377: | AC030-003 | Helm install creates namespace | `kubectl get ns` |\n378: | AC030-004 | Workload Manager receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n379: | AC030-005 | Router receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n380: | AC030-006 | Workload Manager Deployment has configurable replicas | `helm template` inspection |\n381: | AC030-007 | Workload Manager Service exposes correct port | Service YAML inspection |\n382: | AC030-008 | Router has WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL pointing to Workload Manager | Pod env inspection |\n383: | AC030-009 | RBAC ClusterRole contains required permissions | ClusterRole YAML inspection |\n384: | AC030-010 | Optional router RBAC renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n385: | AC030-011 | Optional Volcano scheduler renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n386: | AC030-012 | CRDs present in crds/ directory | Directory inspection |\n387: | AC030-013 | Helm template renders without error | `helm template` exit code |\n388: | AC030-014 | Helm lint passes | `helm lint` exit code |\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Test Strategy\n393: \n394: ### Unit Tests\n395: - Validate Chart.yaml and values.yaml structure\n396: - Test conditional rendering logic in templates\n397: - Verify RBAC rule completeness\n398: - Verify environment variable injection\n399: \n400: ### Integration Tests\n401: - Test `helm install` and `helm upgrade` in a kind cluster\n402: - Verify all resources are created correctly\n403: - Test optional component toggles\n404: - Validate RBAC bindings\n405: \n406: ### Template Validation\n407: - Use `helm template` for rendering tests\n408: - Use `helm lint` for schema validation\n409: - Use `helm diff` for upgrade path testing\n\n(End of file - total 409 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-030\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871486732,"end":1775871486761}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775871486786,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a306b2b001uDrhXkuDE7Lh69","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a305452001vOCdpEE47yh6Jm","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20568,"input":5489,"output":159,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14920}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775871492735,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a30827c0012VQAsCJamyiAan","messageID":"msg_d7a306b58001rfks4BYsdO9aDd","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871494774,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a30866f001uclDhUlwHUU52c","messageID":"msg_d7a306b58001rfks4BYsdO9aDd","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_50ce7e716bdc46e6846dbef0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-023\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n5: - **Language**: Python\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: cmd/cli/\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies\n20: ├── agentcube/\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports\n22: │   ├── cli/\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, invoke/status commands\n25: │   ├── runtime/\n26: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py                  # InvokeRuntime\n27: │   │   └── status_runtime.py                  # StatusRuntime\n28: │   └── services/\n29: │       ├── metadata_service.py                # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n30: │       ├── k8s_provider.py                    # KubernetesProvider\n31: │       └── agentcube_provider.py               # AgentCubeProvider\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### 1.3 Provider Types\n35: \n36: | Provider | Invocation Target | Status Target |\n37: |----------|-------------------|---------------|\n38: | `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR via Router | AgentRuntime CR |\n39: | `k8s` | Kubernetes Service | Kubernetes Deployment |\n40: \n41: ## 2. Command Specifications\n42: \n43: ### 2.1 invoke Command\n44: \n45: The `invoke` command POSTs JSON payloads to deployed agents.\n46: \n47: ```python\n48: def invoke(\n49:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n50:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n51:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n52:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n53:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n54: ) -> None:\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Default Options:**\n58: \n59: | Option | Default |\n60: |--------|---------|\n61: | workspace | \".\" |\n62: | payload | \"{}\" |\n63: | header_list | None |\n64: | provider | \"agentcube\" |\n65: | verbose | False |\n66: \n67: ### 2.2 status Command\n68: \n69: The `status` command retrieves and displays agent deployment status.\n70: \n71: ```python\n72: def status(\n73:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n74:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n75:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n76: ) -> None:\n77: ```\n78: \n79: **Default Options:**\n80: \n81: | Option | Default |\n82: |--------|---------|\n83: | workspace | \".\" |\n84: | provider | \"agentcube\" |\n85: | verbose | False |\n86: \n87: ## 3. Runtime Specifications\n88: \n89: ### 3.1 InvokeRuntime\n90: \n91: Handles agent invocation via HTTP with support for both AgentCube and K8s providers.\n92: \n93: ```python\n94: class InvokeRuntime:\n95:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n96:     \n97:     def invoke(\n98:         self, \n99:         workspace_path: Path, \n100:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n101:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n102:     ) -> Any: ...\n103:     \n104:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n105:     \n106:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n107:         self, \n108:         agent_id: str, \n109:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n110:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], \n111:         endpoint: str, \n112:         workspace_path: Path\n113:     ) -> Any: ...\n114:     \n115:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n116:         self, \n117:         endpoint: str, \n118:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n119:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], \n120:         workspace_path: Path\n121:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n122: ```\n123: \n124: **Invoke Flow:**\n125: \n126: ```\n127: invoke command (provider=agentcube)\n128:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n129:             ├─> _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n130:             │       └─> Returns: endpoint, namespace, agent_name\n131:             └─> _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n132:                     └─> POST to router with session header\n133: \n134: invoke command (provider=k8s)\n135:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n136:             └─> _direct_http_invocation()\n137:                     └─> POST to k8s service URL\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Known Issue**: `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` may raise `UnboundLocalError` if `endpoint` doesn't start with `http`.\n141: \n142: ### 3.2 StatusRuntime\n143: \n144: Retrieves and displays agent deployment status.\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: class StatusRuntime:\n148:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n149:     \n150:     def get_status(\n151:         self, \n152:         workspace_path: Path, \n153:         provider: Optional[str] = None\n154:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n155:     \n156:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n157:     \n158:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Status Flow:**\n162: \n163: ```\n164: status command (provider=agentcube)\n165:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n166:             └─> _get_cr_k8s_status()\n167:                     └─> Query AgentRuntime CR\n168: \n169: status command (provider=k8s)\n170:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n171:             └─> _get_k8s_status()\n172:                     └─> Query Deployment/Service\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## 4. Input Validation\n176: \n177: ### 4.1 Workspace Validation\n178: \n179: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n180: |----------|-----------|--------|\n181: | AR-023-004-A | Workspace path does not exist | Raise `FileNotFoundError` |\n182: | AR-023-004-B | Metadata file not found | Raise `FileNotFoundError` |\n183: | AR-023-004-C | Agent not published (no agent_id) | Print warning, exit code 1 |\n184: \n185: ### 4.2 Payload Parsing\n186: \n187: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n188: |----------|-----------|--------|\n189: | AR-023-002-A | Valid JSON | Convert to Python dict |\n190: | AR-023-002-B | Invalid JSON | Print error, exit code 1 |\n191: | AR-023-002-C | Default \"{}\" | Use empty dict |\n192: \n193: ### 4.3 Header Parsing\n194: \n195: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n196: |----------|-----------|--------|\n197: | AR-023-003-A | Single valid header | Add to request headers |\n198: | AR-023-003-B | Multiple headers | Merge all headers |\n199: | AR-023-003-C | Invalid format (no colon) | Print error, exit code 1 |\n200: | AR-023-003-D | Multiple colons | Split on first colon only |\n201: \n202: ## 5. Provider Integration\n203: \n204: ### 5.1 AgentCube Provider (invoke)\n205: \n206: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n207: |----------|-----------|--------|\n208: | AR-023-005-A | Has agent_endpoint | Use endpoint from metadata |\n209: | AR-023-005-B | Has session_id | Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header |\n210: | AR-023-005-C | k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\" | Rewrite URL to invocations path |\n211: | AR-023-005-D | Missing router_url | Raise `ValueError` |\n212: \n213: **URL Rewrite Logic:**\n214: ```python\n215: if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n216:     base = metadata.agent_endpoint\n217:     endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 5.2 K8s Provider (invoke)\n221: \n222: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n223: |----------|-----------|--------|\n224: | AR-023-006-A | Has k8s_deployment.service_url | Use service URL as endpoint |\n225: | AR-023-006-B | Missing service_url | Raise `ValueError` |\n226: \n227: ### 5.3 AgentCube Provider (status)\n228: \n229: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n230: |----------|-----------|--------|\n231: | AR-023-011-A | CR exists with status | Read status.agentEndpoint |\n232: | AR-023-011-B | CR exists without status | Return \"created_no_status\" |\n233: | AR-023-011-C | CR not found | Return \"not_found_in_k8s\" |\n234: \n235: ### 5.4 K8s Provider (status)\n236: \n237: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n238: |----------|-----------|--------|\n239: | AR-023-012-A | Deployment exists | Return deployment status |\n240: | AR-023-012-B | Deployment not found | Return \"not_found\" |\n241: \n242: ## 6. HTTP Request/Response\n243: \n244: ### 6.1 Request\n245: \n246: - **Method**: POST\n247: - **Content-Type**: application/json\n248: - **Headers**: \n249:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n250:   - `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}` (if available)\n251:   - Custom headers from `--header` option\n252: \n253: ### 6.2 Response Handling\n254: \n255: | Scenario | Response | Action |\n256: |----------|----------|--------|\n257: | AR-023-007-B | Success (2xx) | Print response body |\n258: | AR-023-007-C | Error (4xx/5xx) | Print error in red, exit code 1 |\n259: \n260: ## 7. Output Display\n261: \n262: ### 7.1 Status Table (Rich)\n263: \n264: | Column | Fields |\n265: |--------|--------|\n266: | Field | Agent Name, Provider, Status, Endpoint/Service URL |\n267: | Value | Respective values from metadata and K8s/CR status |\n268: \n269: ### 7.2 Exit Codes\n270: \n271: | Condition | Exit Code |\n272: |-----------|-----------|\n273: | Success | 0 |\n274: | Not published | 1 |\n275: | HTTP error | 1 |\n276: | Invalid payload/header | 1 |\n277: | Exception with verbose | 1 |\n278: \n279: ## 8. Error Handling\n280: \n281: ### 8.1 Error Handling Pattern\n282: \n283: ```python\n284: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n285:     \"\"\"Print error message and optionally full traceback.\"\"\"\n286:     print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", fg=\"red\")\n287:     if verbose:\n288:         traceback.print_exc()\n289:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ### 8.2 Verbose Mode\n293: \n294: - **Given**: `--verbose` flag is enabled\n295: - **When**: An error occurs\n296: - **Then**: Print full traceback along with error message\n297: \n298: ## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n299: \n300: - [ ] AC001: Invoke command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, payload, header, provider, verbose)\n301: - [ ] AC002: Invoke validates JSON payload and exits with code 1 for invalid JSON\n302: - [ ] AC003: Invoke validates header format and exits with code 1 for invalid headers\n303: - [ ] AC004: Invoke adds session header (X-Agentcube-Session-Id) when session_id exists in metadata\n304: - [ ] AC005: Invoke validates agent is published before attempting to invoke\n305: - [ ] AC006: Invoke rewrites URL for AgentRuntime CR deployments\n306: - [ ] AC007: Invoke sends POST request with JSON body and appropriate headers\n307: - [ ] AC008: Status command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, provider, verbose)\n308: - [ ] AC009: Status validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n309: - [ ] AC010: Status returns \"not_published\" and exits with code 1 when agent not published\n310: - [ ] AC011: Status retrieves AgentRuntime CR status for agentcube provider\n311: - [ ] AC012: Status retrieves Deployment status for k8s provider\n312: - [ ] AC013: Status displays results in Rich Table format\n313: - [ ] AC014: Both commands handle errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n314: \n315: ## 10. CLI Options Mapping\n316: \n317: | Command | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n318: |---------|------------|-------------------|------|\n319: | invoke | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n320: | invoke | `--payload` | payload | str (JSON) |\n321: | invoke | `--header` | header_list | Optional[List[str]] |\n322: | invoke | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n323: | invoke | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n324: | status | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n325: | status | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n326: | status | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n327: \n328: ## 11. Dependencies\n329: \n330: ### Required Runtime Dependencies\n331: \n332: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n333: - `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP client\n334: - `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal formatting\n335: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing\n336: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n337: \n338: ### Optional Dependencies\n339: \n340: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0` - K8s client (for status command)\n\n(End of file - total 340 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-023\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies\n├── agentcube/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775871494763,"end":1775871494772}}}}
