{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871558592,"sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a30b52b0019tTgX0um87ls23","messageID":"msg_d7a30a9ae0010jlW9biSrcsUzO","sessionID":"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f9d3d68f8cc64d77aa43dbfd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-030\n- **Module**: manifests\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n- **Stage**: ST-1\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\n\n### 1.2 Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml\n├── values.yaml\n├── crds/\n│   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n    ├── rbac/\n    │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n    │   └── router.yaml\n    └── volcano/\n        └── agent-scheduler.yaml\n```\n\n### 1.3 Components\n\n| Component | Kind | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\n| Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing layer |\n| WorkloadManager RBAC | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding | Yes | Cluster-wide permissions |\n| Router RBAC | ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding | Optional | Namespace-scoped permissions |\n| Volcano Scheduler | Multiple (SA, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) | Optional | Custom scheduler |\n| CRDs | CustomResourceDefinition | Yes | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Chart.yaml\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v2\nname: agentcube\ndescription: A Helm chart for AgentCube\ntype: application\nversion: 0.1.0\nappVersion: 1.0.0\n```\n\n### 2.2 values.yaml Schema\n\n| Path | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n|------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` | No | Image pull secrets |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override chart name |\n| `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override full name |\n| `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` | Yes | Redis address (host:port) |\n| `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` | No | Redis password |\n| `router.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Router replica count |\n| `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | No | Router image |\n| `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n| `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n| `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n| `router.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n| `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` | No | Container port |\n| `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n| `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n| `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n| `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n| `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n| `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` | No | Service account name |\n| `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` | No | Create RBAC |\n| `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Replica count |\n| `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | No | Image repository |\n| `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n| `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n| `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n| `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n| `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n| `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n| `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n| `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n| `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n| `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` | No | Enable scheduler |\n| `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Scheduler replicas |\n| `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` | No | Scheduler image |\n| `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n| `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Workload Manager Service\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nspec:\n  type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n  selector:\n    app: workloadmanager\n  ports:\n    - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n      targetPort: http\n      protocol: TCP\n      name: http\n```\n\n### 3.2 Workload Manager Deployment\n\n| Field | Source | Description |\n|-------|--------|-------------|\n| `replicas` | `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas` | Replica count |\n| `serviceAccountName` | `\"workloadmanager\"` | Fixed SA |\n| `image` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.workloadmanager.image.tag` | Container image |\n| `imagePullPolicy` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | Pull policy |\n| `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n| `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n| `env.AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `.Release.Namespace` | Release namespace |\n| `livenessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n| `readinessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n| `resources` | `.Values.workloadmanager.resources` | Resource limits |\n\n### 3.3 Router Service\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nspec:\n  type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n  selector:\n    app: agentcube-router\n  ports:\n    - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n      targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n      protocol: TCP\n      name: http\n```\n\n### 3.4 Router Deployment\n\n| Field | Source | Description |\n|-------|--------|-------------|\n| `replicas` | `.Values.router.replicas` | Replica count |\n| `serviceAccountName` | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` or `\"agentcube-router\"` | Conditional SA |\n| `image` | `.Values.router.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.router.image.tag` | Container image |\n| `env.WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` | Internal URL |\n| `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n| `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n| `args` | `--debug` if `.Values.router.debug` | Debug flag |\n| `livenessProbe` | `/health/live` | Health endpoint |\n| `readinessProbe` | `/health/ready` | Health endpoint |\n\n### 3.5 Workload Manager RBAC\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters\", \"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"update\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"pods\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\"]\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: workloadmanager\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nroleRef:\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: workloadmanager\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n```\n\n### 3.6 Router RBAC (Optional)\n\nRendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nroleRef:\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n```\n\n### 3.7 Volcano Scheduler (Optional)\n\nRendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n\n| Resource | Name | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| ServiceAccount | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Scheduler SA |\n| ConfigMap | `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` | Scheduler config |\n| ClusterRole | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Full scheduling permissions |\n| ClusterRoleBinding | `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` | RBAC binding |\n| Service | `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` | Scheduler service |\n| Deployment | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Scheduler deployment |\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Validation Errors\n\n| Scenario | Condition | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| AR-030-001-A | Chart.yaml missing/invalid | `helm lint` fails |\n| AR-030-001-B | values.yaml missing keys | Template render failure |\n| AR-030-010-A | `helm lint` fails | Exit code != 0 |\n| AR-030-010-B | Template render error | Helm error message |\n\n### 4.2 Runtime Errors\n\n| Scenario | Condition | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| redis.addr not set | Empty string | Deployment pods will fail |\n| Invalid namespace | Special characters | Helm error |\n| RBAC conflict | Existing role with same name | Helm upgrade fails |\n\n### 4.3 Conditional Rendering Errors\n\n| Scenario | Condition | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| router.rbac.create invalid | Non-boolean | Template type error |\n| volcano.scheduler.enabled invalid | Non-boolean | Template type error |\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\n| Test | Method | Expected Result |\n|------|--------|-----------------|\n| Chart.yaml structure | `helm lint` | Pass with exit code 0 |\n| values.yaml schema | YAML parsing | All keys present |\n| Template syntax | `helm template` | Valid YAML output |\n| Conditional rendering | Override values | Correct resources rendered |\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Environment | Validation |\n|------|-------------|------------|\n| Helm install | kind cluster | Namespace created, all resources deployed |\n| Helm upgrade | Running cluster | No disruption, resources updated |\n| Optional RBAC | `router.rbac.create: true` | Role/RoleBinding created |\n| Optional Volcano | `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true` | Scheduler pods running |\n| Redis env vars | Custom values | Pods have correct env |\n\n### 5.3 Test Commands\n\n```bash\n# Lint check\nhelm lint manifests/charts/base\n\n# Template rendering\nhelm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n  --set redis.password=secret\n\n# Install (requires cluster)\nhelm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --namespace agentcube \\\n  --create-namespace \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis:6379\n\n# Full render with all options\nhelm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true\n```\n\n## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification |\n|----|-----------|--------------|\n| AC030-001 | Chart.yaml with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 | `helm lint` |\n| AC030-002 | values.yaml contains all documented keys | YAML parsing |\n| AC030-003 | Helm install creates namespace | `kubectl get ns` |\n| AC030-004 | Workload Manager REDIS_ADDR env | Pod inspection |\n| AC030-005 | Router REDIS_ADDR env | Pod inspection |\n| AC030-006 | Workload Manager replicas configurable | Template inspection |\n| AC030-007 | Router WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL set | Pod env inspection |\n| AC030-008 | ClusterRole contains required rules | YAML inspection |\n| AC030-009 | Router RBAC conditional rendering | Template render |\n| AC030-010 | Volcano scheduler conditional | Template render |\n| AC030-011 | CRDs in crds/ directory | Directory listing |\n| AC030-012 | Helm template renders without error | Exit code 0 |\n| AC030-013 | Helm lint passes | Exit code 0 |\n\n## 7. Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| Helm | 3.x | Chart rendering and installation |\n| Kubernetes | 1.19+ | API versions used |\n| controller-gen | v0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n\n## 8. Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope:\n\n- Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n- Ingress configuration\n- Prometheus/Grafana monitoring\n- Redis deployment (external)\n- Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n- Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n- Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n- Custom Ingress or NetworkPolicy configurations","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775871558575,"end":1775871558588}}}}
